The body of a teenager was found on Thursday near Black Rock beach on the KwaZulu-Natal north coast - five days after he was swept out to sea. Rescue Care spokesperson Paul Herbst said the 14-year-old boy’s body was found on the beach, about 1km north of where he went swimming. A search and rescue team conducted a search on Thursday morning, using a beach patrol helicopter and all-terrain vehicles. However lifeguards on foot patrol, discovered the boy’s body, said Herbst.